# TEST CONTRACT POLICY (READ BEFORE ANY TEST)

> Full rule: `{rules_dir}/04-testing/contract-first-tests.md` — **read before writing, editing, or deleting any test.**

## Law

Tests are **immutable logical contracts**. They **fail** when code breaks the contract. **Never** change a test to match broken code.

## Forbidden

- Mirror production logic in the test
- Weaken assertions to pass CI
- Tests that cannot fail
- Fix test expectations without contract/doc change

## Pyramid (all automated in CI)

| Type | ~Share | Purpose |
|------|--------|---------|
| **Unit** | 75% | Domain, VOs, state machines |
| **Integration** | 20% | Use cases + adapters |
| **E2E** | 5% | Critical user journeys |

## Before any test

1. Read `contract-first-tests.md`
2. Read contract source (GIVEN/WHEN/THEN, `API-CONTRACT.md`, use case)
3. Write failing test → implement → run automated suite
4. If test vs code conflict → **fix code** (or formal contract change with user)

```bash
./harness/resolve-rules.sh test contract unit e2e
```
